    "Report": "<div><strong>Wednesday, February 25, 2026 </strong>-- <strong>8:00AM<br></strong><br>Following overnight rain, our teams will be conducting a thorough inspection of the mountain this morning to make sure conditions are safe for everyone. All chairs will have a 30-minute delayed opening, and J7 will be further delayed. All runs off of the Face will be closed today -- access to the base will be open via Canyon Trail or downloading J1.<br>There’s a chance of mixed rain and snow early today, with temperatures rising into the mid-40s under mostly cloudy skies.<br>With rain on snow and colder surface temps, conditions are extremely slippery. Please use extra caution when walking around the base area and while driving.<br>Thanks for your patience this morning — safety first so we can all have a great day at June Mountain&nbsp; <br><br><br>Visit our <a href=\"https://www.junemountain.com/mountain-information/safety-and-conduct\">Safety and Conduct</a> page for more info.&nbsp;</div>",
